main event: An unknown object was observed moving at a high rate of speed from west to east over the Atlantic Ocean on September 3, 1962.
interesting points: The object was tracked for approximately 1-2 minutes,The sighting was recorded via both ground-radar and air-intercept radar,The object was classified by the case as a satellite,No photographs are included in the report,The case was part of Project 10073.
sighted object: unknown object moving at high speed
witness description: Observation was made via radar, no eyewitness accounts reported.
